cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper deals with the classification of lung nodules in CT images using convolutional neural networks. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a novel approach to deal with class imbalance, which is a common problem in machine learning, indicating that it could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of neural networks also suggests that it could belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the evaluation of the proposed method involves the use of Free Receiver Operating Characteristics (FROC) curve analysis, which is a common technique in information retrieval, indicating that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
